D=8954.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why are Rains spells resisted more?</span><hr size=1> Here is the link to the raw data spell info for Sirocco on Lucy:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spellraw.html?id=1662&source=Test">lucy.fnord.net/spellraw.h...ource=Test</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The &quot;resistadj&quot; value is 0.<br>
<br>
If you were to check the resistadj value for our standard DD spells, you will notice they are all 0 as well.<br>
<br>
If our Rain spells have a resistadj value of 0, why do we get more full resists (no damage) from them?  I have also noticed that each wave of a rain spell will always hit for the same value.  There are no partial resists for less damage.  Are rain spells coded so that any resist (full or partial), results in no damage?  If so, is there a field in the Lucy table that would indicate this? <br>
<br>
Thanks <p>Kebkin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=551328" target="top">My gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perelandraeldil>Perelandra Eldil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 6:45:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8954.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why are Rains spells resisted more?</span><hr size=1> Rain spell waves can be partially resisted. It has happened to me on multiple occasions, but is by no means frequent.<br>
<br>
From my understanding of the subject, rain spells have a resist check for every wave (and possibly 2 for manastorm). This means a resist has 3 chances to happen instead of the 1 for a DD spell. But counting each wave individually, I see approximately the same resist rate for rains as I do for the same type of DD (magic, fire). Of coarse this is a visual observation, I haven't done the parsing to back up the resist rates. <p>Perelandra Eldil<br>
Mage of Druzzil Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 6:48:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8954.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why are Rains spells resisted more?</span><hr size=1> There was testing done on Graffe's about rain resists, and the conclusion was that rains had about 21% chance of resist in addition to the normal resist chance.<br>
<br>
The test was done against a mob that the tester cast a normal spell with no resist mod on more then 1000 times for 0 resists and then used a rain with -300 resist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abdielalazrad>Abdiel AlAzrad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 7:30:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8954.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~irasfel/_uimages/EVO3_26470.gif Height=151 Width=113></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why are Rains spells resisted more?</span><hr size=1> The standard consensus seems to be that in the general design of the &quot;rain&quot; type spell there is an innate resist chance per wave - some sort of hard-coded difference.  Such a thing could pretty easily not show up in Lucy, as it only shows what's in the dat file.  What happens before the dat could be tinkered with at the design level, and be pretty invisible to us players unless some hardcore programmer utterly deconstructed the EQ code that's on the Sony servers. <p>&lt;BR&gt;<br>
